# State Readability

- Keep setup state, live race state, and result state clearly separated in code.
- Make countdown, running, paused, and finished transitions explicit.
- Derived display labels should not mutate authoritative simulation state.
- When randomness exists, keep the selection path inspectable and easy to trace.
- Keep API payload types and UI state types adjacent when that improves traceability.
